(1, 'WCGN', '+2348157289795', 'wordcentralnetwork@gmail.com', '<h6></h6><h6><b><font style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">LEKKI OFFICE</font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</font></b></h6><b style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">19A, Osapa London,<br>Off Ibeju-Lekki Express Way,<br>Lekki, Lagos, Nigeria.</b><h6><b><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br>---</font></b></h6><h6><b><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"\"><br><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">OSOGBO OFFICE.</span><br><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">RM7, Ascension Shopping Complex,</span><br><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Beside Gandhi Bus Stop, Kobo n gbogbo e Area,</span><br><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Osogbo, Osun State, Nigeria</span><br></font></b></h6><p><br></p>', 1, '<h6><b>\r\n                                If the youths have to\r\n                                become a better version of\r\n                                themselves or better still a\r\n                                splitting imaging of Jesus, we must\r\n                                begin to rid ourselves of the\r\n                                pessimistic phenomenon and build them in the manner of the word of His Grace, for in his light can they truly discover themselves.</b></h6>', '<p>                    <p><a href=\"https://t.me/WCGNetwork/41\" target=\"_blank\">ACCESS ALL ABOUT WCGN IN PDF DOCUMENT</a></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>\r\n                </p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">                    Word Central Global Network (WCN) is a vibrant youth\r\n              ministry dedicated to liberating youths from the shackles\r\n              of perversion, transforming them to be lights in a perverse\r\n              and crooked world, and releasing them as guided missiles\r\n              to impact their world in the  market place; campuses,\r\n              fellowships, Churches, families, etc.\r\n</span></p><h6>              </h6><h6><b><br></b></h6><h6><b>Word Central Global Network, as the name implies, firmly\r\n              believes in the efficacy of the Word of God to transform\r\n              lives and we have seen this happen over the years.</b></h6><p><b>.</b></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Started off in 1999 as Eagle\'s Era, a power meeting which takes place once a month.</span><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The meeting has testimonies of mighty deliverances and miracles following witnessed by the awesome teaching and power ministry of Dr Faith Oniya.</span><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">He was just a young minister of the gospel then yet the meeting endeared him to many youths who came from neighbouring towns and cities; Ilorin, Ajasse, Igosun, Ipee, Adeleke, Offa, Erin Ile and Ijagbo, the hosting city of this meeting.</span><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Dr Faith Oniya began to get a clearer picture of the vision and that has led him to seek more trainings which took him out of the state for years, ministering and being ministered to as he grew in his experience with God and Men.</span><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">He also grew in human management skills serving as project manager and also the technical director in his service in church up until 2016 when the Lord specifically instructed him to leave it all and return to base.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">He has since then pastored in Living Word Evangelical Assembly, and ran this awesome youth ministry under the auspices of the church.</span><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Word Central Global Network is not a fellowship but a youth group with many operational centers across the country with its student base groups on campuses.</span><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The entire journey has been an awesome one for the last 2 decades and counting.</span></p>', '<p> To raise a crop of youths who would catch the fire of\r\n                      the Holy Ghost, come alive, be revived themselves, and then, begin to cause an unstoppable revival in our\r\n                      days towards seeing the continuity of the faith handed\r\n                      us by the fathers and an increase of the same through\r\n                      dedicated and calculated youth meetings, mentorship\r\n                      initiatives and discipleship programs.\r\n                    </p>', '<p> We help youths see the value heaven places on their soul,\r\n                      engage them in active service in God‚Äôs Kingdom, subject\r\n                      them to an environment of leadership and commission\r\n                      them to do the same at the appointed time thus producing\r\n                      men of purpose, focus, discipline, having themselves\r\n                      been products of the same.\r\n                    </p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">                    We believe all members of Word Central Global Network;</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">‚ô™ Must be born again.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">‚ô™Must have a desire to grow spiritually.</span><br><span style=\"color: rgb(37, 47, 64); font-size: 1rem;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">‚ô™Must be willing to be trained and be ready to be functionally versatile.</span></span><br><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">‚ô™Must be dedicated and sacrificial (spiritually and\r\n                    financially), and otherwise.</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">‚ô™Must be ministry-oriented and vision driven</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">‚ô™Must be acquiescent to leadership and strive to\r\n                    be one.</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">‚ô™Must be oriented towards consistent service.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p>', '<blockquote class=\"blockquote\"><p><b><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">‚ÄúWHAT YOU SEE YOU GET‚Äù</span><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\"><br></span></b></p></blockquote><p><br></p><p>There is a lot of noise about how useless, ungodly and at some point, how lazy the youths are. </p><p><br></p><p>Each time I hear this, my heart bleeds simply because it is an established fact that we immediately lose or begin to lose our ability to help whatever we have concluded as damaged and/or ‚Äúuseless‚Äù. </p><p><br></p><p>You have to see the good to get the good. </p><p><br></p><p>What you see you get!</p><p><b><br></b></p><p>If the youths have to become a better version of themselves or better still a splitting image of Jesus for in his light, we must begin to rid ourselves of the pessimistic phenomenon which positions us in a helpless stance to do nothing. Let us introduce Jesus and his love to them for only in his loves can they truly discover themselves. </p><p><br></p><p>If there is no glimmer of hope within us, how can we produce in them hope for their future. </p><p><br></p><p>We cannot give what we do not have.</p><p><b><br></b></p><p>I once said at a youth meeting I had about 20 years ago which I tagged \'Youth Expression<i>\'</i>&nbsp;that </p><p><br></p><p><i>‚Äú‚Ä¶the strength of an entire length of rope is determined by its weakest link‚Ä¶ if we continue to call the youths corrupt and weak, we are indirectly describing our strength, our fate and the product that our best could leave behind. We are exactly what we call them. We cannot be better‚Ä¶‚Äù</i></p><p><br></p><p>It is high time we all arise and get busy helping these young folks discover who they have been created to be in Christ rather than get busy complaining about the ills we observe. </p><p><br></p><p>Afterall, we are exactly what we complain about.</p>\r\n                 \r\n\r\n              \r\n\r\n              \r\n          \r\n\r\n\r\n            <p><!-- The Modal --></p>\r\n      <div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"pioneerModal\"><p>\r\n        </p><div class=\"modal-dialog modal-lg\"><p>\r\n          </p><div class=\"modal-content\"><p>\r\n\r\n            <!-- Modal Header -->\r\n            </p><div class=\"modal-header\"><p>\r\n              </p><p class=\"modal-title\">Message from the Pioneer</p><p>\r\n              <button type=\"button\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\">√ó</button>\r\n            </p></div><p>\r\n\r\n            <!-- Modal body -->\r\n            </p><div class=\"modal-body\"><p>\r\n            <strong> ‚ÄúWHAT YOU SEE YOU GET‚Äù</strong>\r\n            </p><p><b>\r\n                There is a lot of noise about how useless, ungodly and\r\n                at some point, how lazy the youths are.\r\n                Each time I hear this, my heart bleeds simply because it\r\n                is an established fact that we immediately lose or begin\r\n                to lose our ability to help whatever we have concluded as\r\n                damaged and/or ‚Äúuseless‚Äù.\r\n                You have to see the good to get the good.\r\n                What you see you get!\r\n            </b></p><p>\r\n\r\n            </p><p class=\"font-weight-bold quotes \" style=\"  text-align:justify;\">\r\n              If the youths have to become a better version of\r\n              themselves or better still a splitting image of Jesus for\r\n              in his light, can they truly discover themselves, we must\r\n              begin to rid ourselves of the pessimistic phenomenon. If\r\n              there is no glimmer of hope within\r\n              us, how can we produce in them\r\n              hope for their future. We cannot\r\n              give what we do not have.\r\n              </p><p>\r\n\r\n              </p><p class=\"font-weight-bold quotes \" style=\"  text-align:justify;\">\r\n              I once said at a youth meeting\r\n              I had about 20 years ago\r\n              which I tagged ‚ÄúYouth\r\n              Expression‚Äù that\r\n              ‚Äú‚Ä¶the strength of an\r\n              entire length of rope\r\n              is determined by its\r\n              weakest link‚Ä¶ if we\r\n              continue to call the youths corrupt and weak, we are indirectly describing\r\n              our strength, our fate and the product that our best\r\n              could leave behind. We are exactly what we call them.\r\n              We cannot be better‚Ä¶‚Äù\r\n              </p><p>\r\n\r\n              </p><p class=\"font-weight-bold quotes \" style=\"  text-align:justify;\">\r\n              It is high time we all arise and get busy helping these\r\n              young folks discover who they have been created to be in\r\n              Christ rather than get busy complaining about the ills we\r\n              observe. Afterall we are exactly what we complain about.\r\n              </p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n            </p></div><p>\r\n\r\n            <!-- Modal footer -->\r\n            </p><div class=\"modal-footer\"><p>\r\n              <b><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-warning\" data-dismiss=\"modal\">Close</button></b>\r\n            </p></div><p>\r\n\r\n          </p></div><p>\r\n        </p></div><p>\r\n      </p></div>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">        The best gift to the world is the gift of salvation. The best gift to the church is the gift of the word.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">        </span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">We have been sent with a </span><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">message. </span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The devil can‚Äôt shut us up, nothing can stop us.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">We have a message that must be heard, and that message is the word of peace and hope, of rest and of</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">        the finished work.    </span></p>', 'Dr Faith Oniya', 'Dr Faith Oniya', '(Clicking the link above redirects you to the official WCGN Telegram download Platform. Feel free to join us there)', 'https://www.facebook.com/wordcentralglobal-100744302265678/', 'twitter.com', 'linkedin.com', 'https://youtube.com/channel/UChg3tJUsC1JEaNOM5ZtGM3A', 'https://www.instagram.com/invites/contact/?i=11feze0oog3qz&utm_content=8fozudu', 'https://wa.me/message/3ZFXRZ6Y7ENAK1', '2021-10-09 07:36:59', '2021-10-29 15:46:30');

